### 1  You Can

* **Run** ElectronAIChat anywhere, for anything, for free.
* **Study & tweak** the code, add features, change the UI—go wild.
* **Share** your changes or forks publicly (must keep this license in place).

### 2  Please Do

* Keep this license notice and a link back to the main repo.
* Mark clearly if you’ve modified ElectronAIChat.

### 3  You Can’t (Without Permission)

* Charge money for ElectronAIChat itself—e.g. paid downloads, paywalled builds, or subscriptions.
* Offer ElectronAIChat (original or modified) as a hosted or managed service that others can sign up for.
* Bundle ElectronAIChat into another paid product.

> **Consulting/support is totally fine.** Get paid to install, customise, or teach ElectronAIChat as long as your clients don’t get a hosted ElectronAIChat instance run by you.

